Bank of Central Florida
Bank of Central Florida was founded to serve the financial needs of the local marketplace. The Bank is guided by a local Board of Directors with deep roots in the Central Florida area. These Board members have vast knowledge of the local business climate and are driven by their vision for a financial services institution that is focused on client service.
Our bankers understand the local marketplace and can respond to your individual needs in a way you won’t find anywhere else. We take the time to get to know you and your business and then provide the appropriate financial solutions to meet your needs. Our bankers will work as a member of your professional advisory team alongside your CPA, attorney, and financial advisor to help you reach your business and personal financial goals.
Our goal is to bring the Bank to you through leading edge technology and expertise. We don’t just talk about delivering the highest level of service; we are committed to exceeding your expectations in every way. We take a true interest in your success – that is our promise to you.

Dog Dayz Cafe
Healthy, Tasty, and Ethically Sourced!
“Our journey began with a simple goal: to offer our hardworking team wholesome, nourishing, food to fuel their long, yet fulfilling days. But that goal quickly blossomed into something bigger—a mission to enrich the Winter Haven community with food that’s not just good, but good for you.
We handpick organic ingredients whenever possible because we believe that good food should be packed with good stuff. We support our local farmers, from the crisp veggies they grow to the sweet honey they harvest. We’ve teamed up with
Ethos Coffee Roasters
, our friends from the nearby city of Lakeland, to ensure every cup of coffee is as fresh as it is responsibly sourced. It’s all part of how we’re brewing up a healthier, tastier community, one bite and sip at a time.
Dog Days Café is all about good vibes and even better company. We’ve poured our heart into creating a spot that feels like it’s made just for Winter Haven. A Place that’s all about bringing everyone together (furry friends included!), sparking productivity with the perfect brew, or just being the chill spot where you can kick back on a bench with a good book in hand.”

I love serving clients all over Polk County who, among other things, aspire to a work-optional lifestyle. I use an established process to put all the pieces of the puzzle together, by understanding what’s important to you, building personalized strategies to help you reach your goals and partnering with you throughout your life to keep you on track. About Main Street
.entry-header
Main Street Winter Haven’s mission is to develop and preserve the economic, cultural and historic qualities that make downtown the heart of our community. We believe our historic downtown district has a unique character. We celebrate our rich history while reimagining our historic structures for the next generation. Downtown Winter Haven is a place for businesses of all sizes to thrive,  in an atmosphere of innovation and strong community relationships.
In 1995 Winter Haven was designated a
Florida Main Street City
and Main Street Winter Haven, Inc., was established to carry out the
National Main Street Approach
. Dollar for dollar, Main Street has proven itself to be one of the most impactful, cost-effective community revitalization models in the country. The Main Street program was created at a time when many people had moved their business to shopping malls and strip centers, leaving a once vibrant downtown district empty and susceptible to blight. The program grew out of a recognition that a community is only as strong as its core. Historic downtown Winter Haven has seen tremendous improvement in the last 27 years.
Revitalization
and
Reimagining
is hard work, we appreciate our community partners, stakeholders and volunteers.
Main Street Winter Haven, Inc. is a not-for-profit 501(c)(3) organization that involves the entire community in revitalizing downtown.
